== Tectosilicates ==

Tectosilicates, or &quot;framework silicates,&quot; have a three-dimensional framework of silicate tetrahedra with in a 1:2 ratio. This group comprises nearly 75% of the crust of the Earth. Tectosilicates, with the exception of the quartz group, are aluminosilicates. The Nickel–Strunz classifications are 9.F (tectosilicates without zeolitic ), 9.G (tectosilicates with zeolitic ), and 4.DA (quartz/silica group). Below is a list of tectosilicate minerals and their chemical formulas, organized by groups and series:
*Quartz group (silica)
